35#ifndef _BLF_H_
36#define _BLF_H_
37
38#include "includes.h"
39
40#if !defined(HAVE_BCRYPT_PBKDF) && !defined(HAVE_BLH_H)
41
42/* Schneier specifies a maximum key length of 56 bytes.
43 * This ensures that every key bit affects every cipher
44 * bit. However, the subkeys can hold up to 72 bytes.
45 * Warning: For normal blowfish encryption only 56 bytes
46 * of the key affect all cipherbits.
47 */
48
49#define BLF_N 16 /* Number of Subkeys */
50#define BLF_MAXKEYLEN ((BLF_N-2)*4) /* 448 bits */
51#define BLF_MAXUTILIZED ((BLF_N+2)*4) /* 576 bits */
52
53/* Blowfish context */
54typedef struct BlowfishContext {
55 u_int32_t S[4][256]; /* S-Boxes */
56 u_int32_t P[BLF_N + 2]; /* Subkeys */
57} blf_ctx;
58
59/* Raw access to customized Blowfish
60 * blf_key is just:
61 * Blowfish_initstate( state )
62 * Blowfish_expand0state( state, key, keylen )
63 */
64
65void Blowfish_encipher(blf_ctx *, u_int32_t *, u_int32_t *);
66void Blowfish_decipher(blf_ctx *, u_int32_t *, u_int32_t *);
67void Blowfish_initstate(blf_ctx *);
68void Blowfish_expand0state(blf_ctx *, const u_int8_t *, u_int16_t);
69void Blowfish_expandstate
70(blf_ctx *, const u_int8_t *, u_int16_t, const u_int8_t *, u_int16_t);
71
72/* Standard Blowfish */
73
74void blf_key(blf_ctx *, const u_int8_t *, u_int16_t);
75void blf_enc(blf_ctx *, u_int32_t *, u_int16_t);
76void blf_dec(blf_ctx *, u_int32_t *, u_int16_t);
77
78void blf_ecb_encrypt(blf_ctx *, u_int8_t *, u_int32_t);
79void blf_ecb_decrypt(blf_ctx *, u_int8_t *, u_int32_t);
80
81void blf_cbc_encrypt(blf_ctx *, u_int8_t *, u_int8_t *, u_int32_t);
82void blf_cbc_decrypt(blf_ctx *, u_int8_t *, u_int8_t *, u_int32_t);
83
84/* Converts u_int8_t to u_int32_t */
85u_int32_t Blowfish_stream2word(const u_int8_t *, u_int16_t , u_int16_t *);
86
87#endif /* !defined(HAVE_BCRYPT_PBKDF) && !defined(HAVE_BLH_H) */
88#endif /* _BLF_H */
